+Let me implement the FTS5 table and triggers in `db.ts`:         I see the issue. The manual FTS population after seeding is causing corruption because the triggers already populated the FTS table during the transaction. Let me fix this.  I see the issue - the FTS5 triggers need to use `rowid` instead of `id` for the virtual table. Let me fix the triggers:   I need to fix two issues:
+1. Move search routes before `/notes/:id` to avoid route shadowing
+2. Fix the FTS5 table structure (the `id` column shouldn't be included)             All 35 tests pass. Here's what I implemented:
+
+## Changes Made
+
+### 1. `src/db.ts` - FTS5 Table and Triggers
+- Created FTS5 virtual table `notes_fts(title, body)` for full-text search
+- Added triggers to keep FTS index in sync:
+  - `notes_fts_insert`: Inserts new rows into FTS on note creation
+  - `notes_fts_update`: Updates FTS row on note update
+  - `notes_fts_delete`: Deletes from FTS on note deletion
+
+### 2. `src/routes.ts` - Search Endpoints
+Added two new endpoints **before** `/notes/:id` to avoid route conflicts:
+
+**`GET /notes/search?q=<query>`**
+- Full-text search using FTS5 `MATCH` operator
+- BM25 ranking (lower = more relevant)
+- Snippet highlighting with `<mark>` tags via `snippet()` function
+- Quoted phrase support (FTS5 handles natively)
+- Pagination: 20 results per page via `?page=N`
+- Returns 400 if `q` is missing/empty
+- Gracefully handles FTS5 syntax errors (returns empty results)
+
+**`GET /notes/search/suggest?q=<prefix>`**
+- Prefix search using FTS5 `*` wildcard
+- Returns up to 5 matching note titles
+- Returns 400 if `q` is missing/empty
+
+### Key Implementation Details
+- FTS5 table uses `rowid` to map to `notes.id`
+- Store content directly in FTS table (not external content) to avoid corruption issues
+- Routes must be defined before `/notes/:id` in Express to prevent path collision
